## 2. IL2CPP INTEROP & TYPE SYSTEM (2026)

### Type Casting — MANDATORY Patterns
```csharp
// WRONG ❌
var player = (Il2Cpp.Player)someObject;
var rack = someObject as Il2Cpp.Rack;

// RIGHT ✅
var player = someObject.Cast<Il2Cpp.Player>();
var rack = someObject.TryCast<Il2Cpp.Rack>();
if (rack != null) { /* use rack */ }
```

### Type Information
```csharp
// WRONG ❌
var type = typeof(Il2Cpp.Player);

// RIGHT ✅
var type = Il2CppType.Of<Il2Cpp.Player>();
```

### Generic Method Lookup
```csharp
// IL2CPP specializes generics at compile time. To call a generic method:
var method = AccessTools.Method(
    typeof(SomeGenericClass),
    nameof(SomeGenericClass.SomeMethod),
    generics: new[] { typeof(string) }
);
method?.Invoke(instance, new object[] { arg });
```

### Custom Classes Inheriting Unity Types
Every class that inherits from `MonoBehaviour`, `Component`, or Il2Cpp base types MUST:

1. **Have an IntPtr Constructor:**
   ```csharp
   public MyComponent(IntPtr ptr) : base(ptr) { }
   ```

2. **Be Registered in IL2CPP:**
   ```csharp
   ClassInjector.RegisterTypeInIl2Cpp<MyComponent>();
   ```

3. **Use readonly/private fields:**
   ```csharp
   private readonly string _id;
   public string Id => _id;
   ```

### Native Object Handles
```csharp
// WRONG ❌
IntPtr cachedPtr = obj.Pointer;
// Later... obj might be garbage-collected
UsePointer(cachedPtr); // Crash!

// RIGHT ✅
if (obj.Pointer != IntPtr.Zero) {
    UseObject(obj);
}
```

### String Handling in IL2CPP
```csharp
// When calling IL2CPP methods that take strings:
string managedStr = "hello";
Il2CppSystem.String nativeStr = managedStr;

// To get managed string from Il2CppSystem.String:
string back = nativeStr.ToString();
```

