## 4. HARMONY PATCHING — RULES & PATTERNS

### Base Class: SafePatch
All Harmony patches should inherit from or follow the pattern of `SafePatch`:

```csharp
public abstract class SafePatch
{
    protected static IGregLogger Logger { get; }
    protected static IGregHookBus HookBus { get; }

    protected static void TriggerHook(string hookName, params object[] data)
    {
        var payload = new EventPayload { HookName = hookName };
        HookBus.Dispatch(payload);
    }
}
```

### Mandatory Prefix/Postfix Pattern
```csharp
[HarmonyPatch(typeof(TargetClass), nameof(TargetClass.TargetMethod))]
[HarmonyPrefix]
[HarmonyPriority(Priority.High)]
private static bool TargetMethodPrefix(TargetClass __instance, int param1, ref SomeReturn __result)
{
    try
    {
        // NULL-CHECKS FIRST
        if (__instance == null) return true;
        if (__instance.Pointer == IntPtr.Zero) return true;
        if (param1 == null) return true;

        // Early return (skip original): return false;
        // Allow original to run: return true;
        return true;
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        MelonLogger.Error($"TargetMethodPrefix FAILED: {ex.Message}");
        MelonLogger.WriteToLogDetailed(ex, true);
        return true; // Default: let original run (safe fallback)
    }
}

[HarmonyPatch(typeof(TargetClass), nameof(TargetClass.TargetMethod))]
[HarmonyPostfix]
private static void TargetMethodPostfix(TargetClass __instance, ref SomeReturn __result)
{
    try
    {
        if (__instance == null) return;
        if (__instance.Pointer == IntPtr.Zero) return;

        // Modify __result as needed
        if (__result != null && __result.Pointer != IntPtr.Zero)
        {
            // Safe to use __result
        }
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        MelonLogger.Error($"TargetMethodPostfix FAILED: {ex.Message}");
    }
}
```

### Priority Ordering
When multiple mods patch the same method:
```csharp
[HarmonyPriority(Priority.VeryHigh)]   // Runs first
[HarmonyPriority(Priority.High)]       // Runs second
[HarmonyPriority(Priority.Normal)]     // Default
[HarmonyPriority(Priority.Low)]        // Runs fourth
```

### Never Call `original()` from Prefix
```csharp
// WRONG ❌
[HarmonyPrefix]
private static void BadPrefix(TargetClass __instance)
{
    var result = original(__instance); // Undefined behavior!
}

// RIGHT ✅
[HarmonyPostfix]
private static void GoodPostfix(TargetClass __instance, ref ReturnType __result)
{
    // Modify __result here
}
```

