## 6. GREGMOD — C# MOD BASE CLASS

For C# plugin mods (not MelonMod subclasses), use the `GregMod` abstract base:

```csharp
using GregCore.PublicApi;

[GregMod("com.mycompany.mymod", "1.0.0")]
public class MyMod : GregMod
{
    protected override void OnLoad()
    {
        // Called when mod is loaded
        Logger.Msg("MyMod loaded!");

        // Subscribe to hooks
        Api.On("greg.PLAYER.CoinChanged", OnCoinChanged);
        Api.On("greg.SERVER.StatusChanged", OnServerStatusChanged);
    }

    protected override void OnReady()
    {
        // Called after all mods are loaded
        Logger.Msg("MyMod ready!");
    }

    protected override void OnUnload()
    {
        // Called on mod unload or game shutdown
        Logger.Msg("MyMod unloaded!");
    }

    private void OnCoinChanged(EventPayload e)
    {
        Logger.Msg($"Coins: {e.GetValue<int>("from")} -> {e.GetValue<int>("to")}");
    }

    private void OnServerStatusChanged(EventPayload e)
    {
        var serverId = e.GetValue<string>("serverId");
        var newStatus = e.GetValue<string>("newStatus");
        Logger.Msg($"Server {serverId} is now {newStatus}");
    }
}
```

Properties available in GregMod:
- `Logger` — Mod-specific logger
- `Api` — IGregAPI interface (same as `greg` facade)
- `EventBus` — Direct access to event bus
- `Config` — Configuration service

