## 7. LUA MODS (MOONSHARP)

GregCore ships with **MoonSharp** (vendored full source in `lib/MoonSharp/`).

### Basic Lua Mod Template
```lua
-- File: my_mod.lua

-- Hook subscriptions
greg.on("greg.PLAYER.CoinChanged", function(payload)
    print("Coins changed!")
    print("  From: " .. payload.from)
    print("  To:   " .. payload.to)
end)

greg.on("greg.UI.PauseMenu.Opened", function(payload)
    greg.ui.notify("Game paused!")
end)

-- Access APIs
local balance = greg.economy.get_balance(player_id)
greg.economy.add_money(player_id, 1000)

local servers = greg.server.get_all()
for _, server in ipairs(servers) do
    print("Server:", server.id, "Status:", server.status)
end

-- Send messages
greg.network.send_message(recipient_id, "GREETING", { text = "Hello!" })

-- Save/load persistent data
greg.save.persist("my_setting", 42)
local value = greg.save.load("my_setting")
```

### Lua Module Patterns
```lua
-- Tables for organization
local MyModule = {}

function MyModule.initialize()
    print("MyModule initialized")
end

function MyModule.on_server_status_changed(payload)
    -- Handle event
end

greg.on("greg.SERVER.StatusChanged", MyModule.on_server_status_changed)

return MyModule
```

### Async Operations in Lua
```lua
-- Use coroutines for deferred operations
local function async_operation()
    local task = greg.automation.queue({
        type = "UPDATE_INVENTORY",
        itemId = "CPU_001",
        quantity = 5
    })

    -- Wait for task completion
    while not task.is_complete do
        coroutine.yield()
    end

    print("Task done:", task.result)
end

greg.coroutine.start(async_operation)
```

