## 10. RUST MODS (FFI VIA WIN32FFIBRIDGE)

Rust mods are native DLLs that interact with GregCore via the `GameApiTable` FFI contract.

### Rust SDK Layout
Download `greg-rust-sdk.zip` and extract:
```
greg-rust-sdk/
├── Cargo.toml
├── src/
│   ├── lib.rs
│   └── api.rs          # GameApiTable definitions
├── examples/
│   └── hello_mod.rs
└── build.sh            # Compilation script
```

### Basic Rust Mod Template
```rust
// src/lib.rs

use std::ffi::CStr;
use std::ptr::null_mut;

#[repr(C)]
pub struct GameApiTable {
    pub version: u32,
    pub register_event_handler: unsafe extern "C" fn(event_id: u32, handler: *const u8) -> i32,
    pub send_network_message: unsafe extern "C" fn(recipient: *const u8, msg_type: *const u8, payload: *const u8) -> i32,
    pub get_balance: unsafe extern "C" fn(player_id: *const u8) -> i64,
    pub add_money: unsafe extern "C" fn(player_id: *const u8, amount: i64) -> i32,
    // ... more function pointers
}

static mut API: *const GameApiTable = null_mut();

#[no_mangle]
pub extern "C" fn greg_init(api: *const GameApiTable) {
    if api.is_null() {
        return;
    }
    unsafe {
        API = api;
        let api_ref = &*api;
        if api_ref.version < 1 {
            return; // Incompatible version
        }
    }
}

#[no_mangle]
pub extern "C" fn greg_on_event(event_id: u32, payload: *const u8) {
    match event_id {
        1 => handle_player_coin_changed(payload),
        2 => handle_server_status_changed(payload),
        _ => {}
    }
}

fn handle_player_coin_changed(payload: *const u8) {
    if payload.is_null() {
        return;
    }
    // Parse payload and handle event
    println!("Player coins changed!");
}

fn handle_server_status_changed(payload: *const u8) {
    if payload.is_null() {
        return;
    }
    println!("Server status changed!");
}

#[no_mangle]
pub extern "C" fn mod_version() -> *const u8 {
    b"1.0.0\0".as_ptr()
}
```

### Compilation
```bash
cargo build --release
# Output: target/release/my_mod.dll
# Copy to: Data/Mods/my_mod.dll
```

