## 12. FFI/ABI RULES FOR NATIVE MODS (RUST & GO)

The `GameApiTable` struct is the ABI contract. Breaking it breaks all native mods.

### IMMUTABLE RULES
1. **Never reorder fields** — Native code has offset assumptions burned in
2. **Never delete fields** — Old mods will read garbage
3. **Always append new fields to the end** — Safe for backward compatibility
4. **Increment ApiVersion before appending** — Mods must version-check

### Example: Adding a New Field
```csharp
// OLD (v1)
[StructLayout(LayoutKind.Sequential)]
public struct GameApiTable
{
    public uint Version;                          // +0
    public IntPtr RegisterEventHandler;           // +4
    public IntPtr SendNetworkMessage;             // +8
    public IntPtr GetBalance;                     // +12
}

// NEW (v2) - APPEND ONLY
[StructLayout(LayoutKind.Sequential)]
public struct GameApiTable
{
    public uint Version;                          // +0  (unchanged)
    public IntPtr RegisterEventHandler;           // +4  (unchanged)
    public IntPtr SendNetworkMessage;             // +8  (unchanged)
    public IntPtr GetBalance;                     // +12 (unchanged)
    public IntPtr AddMoney;                       // +16 (NEW - appended)
}
```

Rust mods must version-check:
```rust
unsafe {
    let api = &*API;
    if api.version >= 2 {
        // Safe to call AddMoney
        (api.add_money)(player_id_ptr, 1000);
    }
}
```

### EventPayload ABI
```csharp
[StructLayout(LayoutKind.Sequential)]
public struct EventPayload
{
    public uint EventId;                          // +0
    public IntPtr PayloadData;                    // +4/+8 (platform-dependent)
    public uint PayloadSize;                      // +8/+12
    public uint Flags;                            // +12/+16
}
```

**NO PADDING ALLOWED** — The memory layout is critical for native code.

